【喜好篇】


【表达「喜欢」】

be quite fond[fɒnd]喜欢的 of sth. / doing 非常喜欢某人（物）或做某事

    "I' m very fond of you, you know," he said. 他说：“你知道吗，我很喜欢你。” 


I have a strong/clear preference for sth. / doing 更喜欢某物

    I have a strong preference for sweet food over spicy. 比起辛辣食物我喜欢甜食要多得多。 


adore[əˈdɔː(r)]喜爱 sb. / sth. / doing sth. 非常喜欢某人或某物或做某件事

    Don't you just adore lying in a hot bath? 你难道不喜欢泡热水澡吗？ 


have a strong desire/yearning[ˈjɜːnɪŋ] 渴望 for sth. / doing 对…十分渴望

    I suppose it's because I live in a crowded city that I have a strong yearning for open spaces. 我想是因为我居住在一个拥挤的城市里，所以才会强烈渴望开阔的空间。 


I have a particular[pəˈtɪkjʊlə(r)] 特别的 liking for sth. / doing特别喜欢某物

    I'm having a particular liking for jazz. 我渐渐喜欢上了爵士乐。 


It's a great/huge pleasure to do sth. 做某事很愉悦

    It was such a pleasure to meet you. 见到你很荣幸。 


be crazy about sth. / doing为…而疯狂

    She is completely crazy about her boyfriend. 她对她的男朋友十分着迷。 


be much into sth. / doing 非常喜欢某人（物）或做某事

be passionate[ˈpæʃənət]热情的 about sth. / doing 对…非常热衷

    He is passionate about baseball. 他非常喜欢打棒球。 



【表达「不喜欢」】

don't like…at all 一点都不喜欢

    I order juice every time when I am in a coffee store, because I don't like the taste of coffee at all . 每次来咖啡店我都只点果汁，因为我一点都不喜欢咖啡的口感。 


loathe[ləʊð] 厌恶 sb. / sth. 厌恶某人或某事

    From an early age, the brothers have loathed each other .自小时候起，兄弟俩就一直相互厌恶。 


have a huge/strong/deep aversion[əˈvɜːʃn]厌恶 to sth. 对某物厌倦排斥

    She has a deep aversion to getting up early in the morning. 她非常不愿意一大早起床。 


can't stand sb. / sth. 不能容忍某人或某事 / can't stand sb. doing sth. 不能容忍某人做某事

    I can't stand obnoxious[əbˈnɒkʃəs] 讨厌的 guys who always have to dominate [ˈdɒmɪneɪt] 控制，支配 the conversation. 我受不了那些说话总是逼逼叨个没完的讨厌的人。 


be reluctant[rɪˈlʌktənt]不情愿的 to do sth. 不愿意去做某事

    I was having such a good time, and I was reluctant to leave . 我玩得很开心，都不愿意离开了。 


