【资源环境篇】

资源短缺

water shortage [ˈʃɔːtɪdʒ] 水资源短缺

oil shortage 石油短缺

    The nature resources自然资源 are in short supply 处于短缺的状态中 


使用可再生能源

renewable resources 可再生资源

solar['səulə] energy 太阳能

    More and more families start to use the solar panels [ˈpænl]（太阳能电池板） to collect solar energy. 

wind energy 风能

    The solar and wind energy is clean energy清洁能源 which doesn't produce any emissions [ɪˈmɪʃn]排放 

tidal[ˈtaɪdl] energy 潮汐能


资源短缺原因

the resources are quite limited 资源有限

sb. use sth. wastefully 浪费地adv. 使用浪费

    People always use water and electricity wastefully. 


环境污染

垃圾污染

    A lot of garbage [ˈɡɑːbɪdʒ] 垃圾 has been disposed of just on the side of streets.
    sth. be disposed [dɪˈspəʊz] of 某物被扔掉了 

多多使用可循环材料制作的产品

reusable [ˌriːˈjuːzəbl] material [məˈtɪəriəl] / recyclable [ˌriːˈsaɪkləbl] material 可循环材料

    In order to reduce pollution减少污染 , people need to have an tendency[ˈtendənsi] to 倾向于做某事 buy and use the consumer goods and products消费类产品 made of reusable material可循环材料 


空气污染

car emissions [ɪˈmɪʃn] 汽车尾气排放

polluting gases 污染废气

industrial [ɪnˈdʌstriəl] wasted gases 工业废气

    Large amounts of大量的 industrial wasted gases工业废气 are discharged [dɪsˈtʃɑːdʒ] 排放 daily. 


空气污染会导致

global[ˈɡləʊbl] warming 全球变暖

greenhouse effect [ɪˈfekt] 温室效应

acid[ˈæsɪd] rain 酸雨

    Air pollution can cause irreversible[ˌɪrɪˈvɜːsəbl] damage [ˈdæmɪdʒ] to 导致不可逆的破坏 the environment , and it is causing global warming, greenhouse effect, and acid rain. 


使用清洁能源

clean energy 清洁能源

    The solar and wind energy which don't produce any emissions排放 should be encouraged to use. 

hybrid[ˈhaɪbrɪd] cars 混合动力汽车电动汽车

    Car manufacturers should make an effort to努力做某事 develop the electric [ɪˈlektrɪk] cars电动汽车 and hybrid[ˈhaɪbrɪd] cars 混合动力汽车 . 


人类行为对生态的破坏

upset the ecosystem [ˈiːkəʊsɪstəm] 扰乱生态系统

    Human activities人类的活动 have caused damage to the environment and upset the ecosystem greatly. 


人们在以环境为代价来获取利益

make profits [ˈprɒfɪt] 获取利益

at the expense支出 of sth. 以……为代价

    People are increasingly [ɪnˈkriːsɪŋli] 在不断增加地 making profits at the expense of the environment. 


